# =============================================================================
# Convex Deployment Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
# These secrets live ON the Convex deployment, NOT in `.env.local`.
# They're set via the Convex CLI or dashboard and are read by your
# Convex functions at runtime.
#
# `npm run setup` writes all of them for you on first run. If you're
# configuring by hand, the CLI commands for each variable are inline
# below.
#
# View what's currently set:
#     npx convex env list
#
# For production, add `--prod` to every `npx convex env set` command.

# =============================================================================
# 1. Required — auth and CORS
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SITE_URL — your app's base URL
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used for CORS allowed-origins on the public HTTP endpoints (/api/health,
# /api/users) AND as Better Auth's `baseURL` for redirect construction.
# Must match the origin the browser uses to load your app.
#
#     npx convex env set SITE_URL http://localhost:3000
#
SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET — session signing secret
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 32-byte base64 secret. Better Auth uses it to sign session cookies and
# JWTs. Generate one with:
#
#     npx convex env set BETTER_AUTH_SECRET $(openssl rand -base64 32)
#
# Never commit a real value. Never share it. Rotating it invalidates
# every active session and signs everyone out.
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=<32-byte base64 secret>

# =============================================================================
# 2. Required — Resend (transactional email)
# =============================================================================
# Without these, every auth OTP send fails at runtime: sign-up verification,
# sign-in OTP, password reset, email change. Sign up at https://resend.com
# (free tier covers ~3,000 emails/month).

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RESEND_API_KEY — your Resend API key
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create one at https://resend.com/api-keys (starts with `re_`).
#
#     npx convex env set RESEND_API_KEY re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EMAIL_FROM — `From:` header on outbound auth emails
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Format: "Display Name <address@domain.com>". For dev you can use
# Resend's onboarding sender. For production you must verify your own
# domain at https://resend.com/domains and use an address on it.
#
#     npx convex env set EMAIL_FROM "App <onboarding@resend.dev>"
#
EMAIL_FROM=App <onboarding@resend.dev>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# APP_NAME — brand name shown in email subjects and bodies
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subjects look like: "<APP_NAME>: Verify your email (123456)"
#
#     npx convex env set APP_NAME "Your App"
#
APP_NAME=Your App

# =============================================================================
# 3. Optional — Resend extras
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RESEND_TEST_MODE — restrict sends to @resend.dev addresses
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Defaults to `true` in convex/email.ts. While true, Resend will only
# deliver to @resend.dev addresses (great for dev, blocks accidental
# emails to real users). Flip to `false` once you've verified a sending
# domain at https://resend.com/domains.
#
#     npx convex env set RESEND_TEST_MODE false
#
RESEND_TEST_MODE=true

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET — verifies signatures on /resend-webhook
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required only if you've configured a Resend webhook for delivery
# tracking. Without it, the /resend-webhook endpoint will reject all
# events. See the "Resend Webhook (Optional)" section of README.md for
# the full setup walkthrough.
#
#     npx convex env set RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET whsec_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
</file>

